assetProfile.longBusinessSummary: KITA KOUDENSHA Corporation engages in indoor wiring and power-related construction businesses in Japan. It undertakes electric work, pipe work, air conditioning control device installation work, steel structure work, machinery/equipment installation work, telecommunication work, firefighting facility work, water supply facility work, civil engineering work, and construction work, as well as provides related planning, design, maintenance, maintenance, management, and consulting services. The company is also involved in the construction of transmission line, underground line, and transmission/transformation communication work; indoor wiring work business; electric power related construction business; FA housing environment equipment business; and industrial equipment business. In addition, it offers generators, transformers, electric motors, and elevators; telephone exchanges and electronic calculators; and gas turbine engines, diesel engines and stationary cranes, and package air conditioners. Further, the company manufactures and sells mediation of air conditioning equipment, such as wind blowers; pipe construction equipment, including boilers and pumps; and housing equipment comprising lighting equipment and ventilator fans, computers for information processing, various electric wires, and electric wires and accessories. Additionally, it is involved in the construction of solar power generation equipment and hydroelectric power generation business, as well as operation management, maintenance, and inspection management business. KITA KOUDENSHA Corporation was founded in 1897 and is based in Sapporo, Japan.
